Detailed Description

PobProto class. This class allow to set the pin of the pob-proto board. The pob-proto board have 3 port : A,C and D. You can set this port as input/output or servomotor for control your robot.

  • First set the pins of the board with the methods :
    1. configPortAAs() or configPortAAsAnalogic()
    2. configPortCAs()
    3. configPortDAs()

  • Next, call writeConfig() or writeTinyConfig() (if you have Tiny POB-PROTO board) for write the configuration on the POB-PROTO

  • Finally, you can get/set value of the port.

Warning:
Only the PortC command servomotor and only the PortA can be set as analogic
Author:
Baptiste Burles. POB-Technology
